From 16e0ecd1a5649959f5c6a68bb9188d63a4766865 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrew Miller <soc1024@illinois.edu>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 12:36:44 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] CPU-GPU bitwise parity: standard transformers + Qwen3.5
 hybrid Mamba

Full bitwise tensor match between GPU (RTX 3090/CUDA 12.8) and CPU
(x86-64 with FMA) for IQ4_XS and Q4_K_M quantization formats across
both standard transformer and hybrid Mamba/linear-attention architectures.

Verified models:
- Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-IQ4_XS: 18375/18375 tensors (standard transformer)
- Qwen3.5-4B-IQ4_XS (unsloth): 15246/15246 tensors (hybrid Mamba)
- Qwen3.5-4B-IQ4_XS (heretic): 15246/15246 tensors (hybrid Mamba)
- qwen2.5-3b Q4_K_M: full match (dense + MoE)

Key changes:
- Portable math: expf_det, sincosf_det, powf_int_det, silu_det, logf_det
- Deterministic dot products: IQ4_XS, Q5_K, Q8_0, IQ4_NL, F32
- CPU attention matching GPU fattn-vec warp structure
- F32 matmul serialization (bypass cuBLAS in deterministic mode)
- Deterministic solve_tri, sum_rows, L2 norm, SSM conv
- mrope powf_int_det for hybrid architectures
- exp/expm1 unary op deterministic guards
- gated_delta_net.cu portable expf
- Q8_0 dot product: 4-thread-per-block structure matching GPU mmvq

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
