+# Deterministic Seed Verification
+
+**Prove that a specific LLM output is genuine — not cherry-picked or edited.**
+
+Run a model on GPU with a seed, get interesting output, publish the seed.
+Anyone with a CPU can verify they get the exact same output, bit-for-bit.
+
+## How it works
+
+This fork of llama.cpp achieves **bitwise-identical output** between CUDA GPU
+and x86 CPU for the same (model, seed, prompt, temperature). 18 separate fixes
+across transcendentals, FMA patterns, quantization, attention, and RoPE make
+every intermediate tensor match exactly.
+
+## Quick start
+
+### Docker (easiest — no build needed)
+
+```bash
+# Build the verifier image
+docker build -t det-verify -f tools/det-diag/Dockerfile .
+
+# Download model (Q4_K_M, 2GB)
+# e.g., huggingface-cli download Qwen/Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct-GGUF \
+#        qwen2.5-3b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf --local-dir ./models
+
+# Verify a seed
+docker run --rm -v $(pwd)/models:/models det-verify \
+  -m /models/qwen2.5-3b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf \
+  -p "Once upon a time" -n 30 --seed 2024 --temp 0.7 --deterministic
+```
+
+### Native build
+
+```bash
+cmake -B build \
+  -DGGML_CUDA=OFF -DGGML_DETERMINISTIC=OFF \
+  -DGGML_CPU_REPACK=OFF -DGGML_LLAMAFILE=OFF \
+  -DGGML_NATIVE=OFF -DGGML_AVX2=OFF -DGGML_AVX=OFF \
+  -DGGML_FMA=OFF -DGGML_F16C=OFF \
+  -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="-mfma" -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="-mfma"
+cmake --build build --target llama-det-diag -j$(nproc)
+
+build/bin/llama-det-diag \
+  -m models/qwen2.5-3b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf \
+  -p "Once upon a time" -n 30 --seed 2024 --temp 0.7 --deterministic
+```
+
+### Verify script
+
+```bash
+./tools/det-diag/verify.sh \
+  models/qwen2.5-3b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf \
+  2024 0.7 \
+  "Once upon a time" \
+  ", a little mouse used to go to the cinema every Saturday"
+```
+
+## Example verified seeds
+
+Model: `qwen2.5-3b-instruct-q4_k_m.gguf` (Q4_K_M, SHA256: check with `sha256sum`)
+
+| Seed | Temp | Prompt | Output |
+|------|------|--------|--------|
+| 2024 | 0.7 | "Once upon a time" | ", a little mouse used to go to the cinema every Saturday. But when the pandemic hit, the cinema was closed." |
+| 42 | 0.7 | "Once upon a time" | ", there was a boy named Ivan. Ivan loved to play in a forest and explore new places." |
+| 777 | 0.7 | "Once upon a time" | ", there was a king who had a problem. He had a very powerful, but unfaithful, minister" |
+| 9999 | 0.7 | "Once upon a time" | ", a king decided to build a tower of blocks. Each block was of the same size." |
+
+## How: 18 phases of fixes
+
+Every CUDA transcendental (expf, sinf, cosf, powf, rsqrtf) differs from glibc
+by 1 ULP. Every FMA auto-contraction by the compiler differs between NVCC and
+GCC. The GPU JIT (ptxas) restructures arithmetic per kernel template parameter.
+x86 SIMD quantization uses reciprocal multiply where GPU uses direct division.
+
+All of these are fixed with portable math implementations, explicit FMA control,
+and GPU kernel constraints. See the commit history for details.
+
+## Requirements
+
+- x86-64 CPU with FMA support (any Intel Core since Haswell / AMD since Piledriver)
+- ~4GB RAM for the 3B model
+- GPU side: NVIDIA with CUDA (tested on RTX 3090 / SM86)
+
+## Supported models
+
+Currently verified for **Q4_K_M** quantization (uses Q4_K and Q6_K weight types).
+Other quantization types (IQ4_XS, Q5_K, Q8_0) need additional deterministic
+dot product implementations.
